a terminal command that was made for fun.. This was made using swift so yea.. btw You can run "1nputReturn" and see all of the commands. ## Documentation Documentation of 1nputReturn To start using 1nputReturn run `1nputReturn`. It will show you the main menu. You can do `1nputReturn GET COMMANDS` to see all of the command because this documentation is showing limited commands. ### Commands - `1nputReturn DISABLE ` disables a package or a support. **Requires InputReturnDiskSupport**. - `1nputReturn ENABLE ` enables a package or a support
**Requires InputReturnTweakingSupport and InputReturnDiskSupport** - `1nputReturn GET ` gets the loader image and prints it out. **Requires loaderSupport** - `1nputReturn REMOVE <1nputReturnDisk>` removes an 1nputReturn disk/folder.**Requires loaderSupport** ### Packages - `loaderSupport` package that supports InputReturnDiskSupport. Disabling this will disable InputReturnDiskSupport. - `InputReturnDiskSupport` package that makes complex commands compatible with `#LOADER_SYNC`. -`InputReturnTweakingSupport` package will support tweaking 1nputReturn disks.
